Analysis of various factors influencing customer ratings for restaurant in respect to Zomato Dataset¶

1. Introduction¶

1.1 Business Overview¶

India is well-known for its diverse multi-food cuisine, which can be found in a variety of places. In India, the restaurant business is constantly evolving. In India, a growing number of people are warming up to the concept of consuming restaurant food, whether they eat it in or have it delivered.

Fusion Dining Pvt. Ltd. is a restaurant chain based in India. It is undergoing a difficult period as its restaurant ratings are steadily declining. Fusion Dining aims to take preventative actions in order to improve its ratings. As an analyst team, we will examine Zomato restaurant data and uncover numerous restaurant characteristics elements that may assist Fusion Dining in improving their rating and generating a profit.

1.2 Purpose of the Project¶

1.2.1 Audience¶

The project will assist the management of Fusion Dining Pvt Ltd. in deciding which factors and features are important in the restaurant to gain higher ratings.

1.2.2 The Purpose¶

The basic goal behind evaluating the data is to gain a good sense of the aspects that influence a restaurant's aggregate ranking. In order to respond to the many questions that can be addressed, data analytics is required. The following are some of the questions:

  1. Which restaurants have the best reviews?
  2. What cuisines are available at these highly rated restaurants?
  3. What services does restaurants provide that are highly related to customer ratings?
  4. How do elements like location, food, delivery, average cost, and pricing range affect the restaurant's rating?

1.3 Why this question is important?¶

A multitude of issues must be considered while operating a restaurant business. This study will aid the organization in identifying what features management should add when developing their restaurant's traits by studying numerous restaurant characteristics, restaurant ratings, and other key considerations. This research will help the company better understand their target audience's food preferences, spending power, and what factors lead to higher customer satisfaction ratings.

1.4 The brief summary of findings¶

The restaurant industry in India is expanding. There are many restaurants in India, however the market is not yet saturated. One of the restaurants in India is Fusion Dining. They have a network of branches across India. Recently, the restaurant's manager noticed a problem with declining ratings. This project will assist the analyst team in improving the many characteristics of the restaurant. According to the findings of our project, online delivery, table booking options, cuisines such as North Indian, and the location of the restaurant all play a vital role in increasing the restaurant's ratings.

2. Main¶

Data Cleaning - Data Cleaning is the process of detecting and correcting inaccurate records from the dataset Data Processing - Data Processing is the manupulation of the items of data to product meaningful information

2.1. Description of the dataset including the list of fields¶

Kaggle provided the data set for this project. This Zomato dataset contains a large amount of data from Indian restaurants and includes the following factors: There are 211944 rows and 26 columns in this table. The following features can be found in the details:

  1. Restaurant Id: Each restaurant's unique identifier in numerous cities throughout the world.
  2. Restaurant Name: The restaurant's name.
  3. Country Code: This is the country where the restaurant is located.
  4. City: The location of the eatery.
  5. Address: The restaurant's address
  6. Locality: The location of the building in relation to the rest of the city.
  7. Locality Verbose: Description of the area in detail - Longitude: The location of the restaurant's longitude coordinates
  8. Latitude: The restaurant's location's latitude coordinate.
  9. Cuisines: The restaurant's menu includes a variety of cuisines.
  10. Average The cost for two people is: In two distinct currencies, the cost for two persons
  11. Currency: Currency of the country
  12. Has Table booking: yes/no
  13. Has Online delivery: yes/ no
  14. Is delivering: yes/ no
  15. Switch to order menu: yes/no
  16. Price range: range of price of food
  17. Aggregate Rating: Average rating out of 5
  18. Rating color: depending upon the average rating color
  19. Rating text: text on the basis of rating of rating
  20. Votes: Number of ratings casted by people

Link of the dataset : https://www.kaggle.com/shrutimehta/zomato-restaurants-data

We will deliver this complex pie chart to you in a simple manner. Let's divide this graph into two price ranges: 0 - 900 and 1000 - 2000.

  1. Based on a scale of 0 to 900, 92.45 percent of people eat out.
  2. 7.55 percent of people between the price range of 1000 and 2000 eat out.

2.3 Diagnostic Analytics¶

Diagnostic analytics is a form of advanced analytics that examines data or content to answer the question, Why did it happen? It is characterized by techniques such as drill-down, data discovery, data mining and correlations.Diagnostic Analytics helps us to know why a trend is developed or why a problem occurred. It helps us making inaccurate guesses.

The major factor affecting the ratings of the restaurant are:

  1. cost for two
  2. online delivery service
  3. cuisines
  4. location

2.4 Evidence and Hypothesis:¶

Kivela, Reece, and Inbakaran (1999) studied the difference in the ratings of restaurant attributes based on the demographic characteristics of respondents. In this exhaustive study on restaurants, they divided the restaurants into four categories based on their differentiation in price, location, theme/ambience, service level, cuisine and style. They argued that determinants in restaurant selection vary across age groups, income levels, and restaurant types.

1. H1 - There is a positive relationship between the location of a restaurant and its overall rating.¶

2. H2 - There is a positive relationship between the cost of food and the overall rating.¶

3. H3 - There is a positive relationship between cuisines and overall ratings.¶

4. H4 - There is a positive relationship between food delivery service and overall satisfaction.¶

3 Conclusion¶

3.1 Summary of the Findings¶

  1. India has the highest number of restaurants listed in Zomato. Delhi is the largest city with the maximum number of restaurants listed in the dataset.
  2. North Indian is the most demanded cuisines
  3. Majority of Indian restaurants have price range between 0-750 and 750- 1500.
  4. Majority of restaurants do not have online delivery service
  5. Average cost for two people is under Rs.2000

3.2 Business Implication for Audience¶

Based on our analysis, we were able to conclude that there is a relationship between location and ratings of the restaurant. We also conclude that there is relationship between online delivery and ratings of restaurant. We see that price for the food plays an important part in customer ratings. If price for the food is too high people tend to buy less and rate low.

3.3 Limitation of the project¶

The dataset posed the followed limitations:

  • The data within the variable within this data set is categorical and not numerical. Thus, using regression analysis is difficult to conduct.
  • Large number of restaurant were not rated
  • The dataset was restricted to cuisines only. It lacked the information for dishes in the cuisines

3.4 Potential Project¶

Our analysis will assist not only restaurants, but also organizations looking to invest in the restaurant or cloud kitchen industry. This analysis will produce the best results, upon which the rating elements will be based. The analysis will assist you with several elements such as location, cuisines, delivery, online booking, pricing range, and cost for two people. And also to get accurate result Machine Learning with model processing can be helpful.
